doc.ContractDescription: WE PROPOSE TO IMPROVE THE UTILITY OF A NOW AVAILABLE NEW GENERATION BI DECADAL GLOBAL OCEAN STATE ESTIMATE FOR UNDERSTANDING REGIONAL SEA LEVEL VARIABILITY IN TERMS OF RELEVANT FORCING, LOCAL STORAGE, ADVECTION AND OTHER DYNAMICAL PROCESSES, AND THE PARTITION OF THE OBSERVED CHANGES INTO STERIC AND NON STERIC CONTRIBUTIONS, AND FOR QUANTIFYING UNCERTAINTY IN THE ESTIMATED SPATIAL PATTERNS OF SEA LEVEL VARIABILITY SUBELEMENT 1 OF NRA. THE WORK WILL FURNISH TOOLS TO NASAS DISTRIBUTED ACTIVE ARCHIVE CENTER DAAC IN TERMS OF DATA CONSTRAINED VALUE ADDED PHYSICAL FIELDS THAT ENABLE DETAILED, ACCURATE BUDGET ANALYSIS FOR SEA LEVEL CHANGE STUDIES SUBELEMENT 3 OF NRA. THE OBJECTIVES WILL BE ACHIEVED THROUGH FURTHER INTEGRATION INTO THE ESTIMATION SYSTEM OF ELEMENTS THAT HAVE NOT YET BEEN CONSIDERED BUT ARE RELEVANT COMPONENTS TO THE SEA LEVEL PROBLEM. THESE IMPROVEMENTS WILL HELP TO BRIDGE THE GAP BETWEEN GLOBAL DECADAL STATE ESTIMATES AND THEIR UTILITY FOR DETAILED REGIONAL SEA LEVEL ANALYSES E.G., TARGETING THE WESTERN NORTH ATLANTIC IN THE VICINITY OF THE US EAST COAST, AND TO ASSESS THE IMPACT OF FORCING UNCERTAINTIES ON SEA LEVEL VARIABILITY. THE ESTIMATION SYSTEM ARGUABLY REPRESENTS THE MOST COMPREHENSIVE JOINT USE OF HETEROGENEOUS DATA STREAMS FROM AVAILABLE SATELLITE AND IN SITU DATA, AND REQUIRING COMPREHENSIVE ASSESSMENT OF UNCERTAINTIES IN THE DATA, THE CONTROLS, AND THE RESIDUAL MISFITS TO DATA. WE PROPOSE WORK IN THREE SPECIFIC, RELATED OVERALL OBJECTIVES, 1, WE WILL FOCUS ON INTEGRATION OF EXISTING DATA SETS AND FORCINGS, AND ASSOCIATED SCIENCE NOT YET EXPLORED, NAMELY, THE USE OF TIME VARYING GRACE DATA TO CONSTRAIN MASS TRANSPORT VARIATIONS AND TO COMPLEMENT ALTIMETRY AND ARGO, THE USE OF TIME VARYING FRESHWATER FLUX ESTIMATES RUNOFF PLUS SOLID DISCHARGE FROM CONTINENTAL RIVERS, POLAR ICE SHEETS AS WELL AS GICS, AND THEIR IMPACT ON GRAVITATIONALLY SELF CONSISTENT SEA LEVEL PATTERNS, THE INCLUSION OF SELF ATTRACTION AND LOADING SAL EFFECTS AND ASSESSMENT OF THEIR DYNAMICAL IMPACT ON SEA LEVEL, AND THE ADDITION OF GEOTHERMAL FLUX FORCING TO IMPROVE REPRESENTATION OF ABYSSAL OCEAN IN STERIC SEA LEVEL BUDGET. 2, WE WILL CONDUCT SYSTEMATIC MODEL EXPERIMENTS TO ASSESS THE IMPACT OF INPUT VARIABLE UNCERTAINTIES, SUCH AS INITIAL CONDITIONS, SURFACE FORCINGS, AND MIXING PARAMETERS ON SPATIAL SEA LEVEL PATTERNS. THE EXPERIMENTS ARE BASED ON ALREADY EXISTING PRIOR UNCERTAINTY ESTIMATES REQUIRED FOR THE LEAST SQUARES OPTIMIZATION PROCESS, AND THE AVAILABILITY OF THE ADJOINT OR DUAL STATE OF THE STATE ESTIMATE WITH RESPECT TO SEA LEVEL RELATED METRICS, INCLUDING MEASURES OF REGIONAL CHANGES IN THE WESTERN NORTH ATLANTIC. 3, WE WILL PRODUCE A DRASTICALLY ENHANCED SET TO BE DISSEMINATED VIA NASAS DAAC OF PHYSICAL FIELDS OF THE STATE ESTIMATE THAT ARE NEEDED TO ENABLE MORE DETAILED, ACCURATE BUDGET CALCULATIONS THAN THOSE CURRENTLY AVAILABLE FROM REANALYSIS PRODUCTS OR CMIP SIMULATIONS. THESE ARE MADE POSSIBLE THROUGH THE DYNAMICAL CONSISTENCY OF THE ESTIMATION PROCESS. THE INTENDED DIAGNOSTIC FIELDS WILL FACILITATE UNDERSTANDING OF ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION OF STERIC AND NON STERIC CHANGES IN TERMS OF LOCAL AND REMOTE FORCING, ADVECTION AND DIFFUSION OF DENSITY ANOMALIES, AND PATHWAYS OF OF ANOMALY PROPAGATION THAT ARE CONSISTENT WITH OBSERVATIONS

doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROPOSAL SEEKS CONTINUING FUNDS TO MAINTAIN AND EXPAND THE OPERATION OF THE MINOR PLANET CENTER (MPC) AT THE SMITHSONIAN ASTROPHYSICAL OBSERVATORY. THE MPC IS THE WORLD'S CLEARING HOUSE FOR MINOR PLANET AND COMET DATA, WITH A SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON THE OBSERVATIONS AND SUBSEQUENT SHORT-TERM IMPACT PREDICTIONS OF NEAR-EARTH OBJECTS (NEOS) WITH THE EARTH. AS THE DATA RATE INTO THE MPC INCREASES, THE MPC MUST MAINTAIN OUR 24-HOUR OR LESS TURNAROUND TIME FOR ALL NEO OBSERVATIONS. NEW NEOS MUST BE POSTED AND UPDATED ON OUR WEB PAGES IN NEAR REAL TIME, AND EACH NEW NEO MUST BE CHECKED FOR POSSIBLE SHORT-TERM IMPACTS WITH THE EARTH. FUNDS ARE REQUESTED TO EXPAND MPC STAFF BY ANOTHER FTE, SPECIFICALY IN THE AREA OF IT SERVICES, TO FACILITATE FURTHER AUTOMATION AND IMPROVEMENT OF MUCH OF THE MPC'S EXISTING 1+ MILLION LINES OF CODE. AMONG THE MOST IMPORTANT AREAS OF FOCUS DURING THE 5-YEAR PROPOSAL CYCLE WILL BE UPDATING AND IMPROVING THE MPC'S SOFTWARE TO MINITOR ALL INCOMING SUBMISSIONS OF NEOS FOR POSSIBLE IMPACTS WITH THE EARTH IN THE NEXT FEW DAYS OR WEEKS. ANOTHER AREA OF FOCUS WILL BE MAKING BOTH THE SOFTWARE AND HADWARE AS ROBUST AS POSSIBLE, WITH THE GOAL OF HAVING THE MPC RUN AS CONTINUOUSLY AND ROBUSTLY AS ANY SPACECRAFT. ADDITIONALLY, THE MPC WILL DEVOTE SIGNIFICANT EFFORT TO IMPROVING COMMUNICATION WITH THE PROFEESSIONAL AND PUBLIC COMMUNITIES AT LARGE. WE INTEND TO USE A MIX OF PERSONAL WEB PAGES AND SOFTWARE, STANDARD SOCIAL MEDIA TECHNIQUES, AND ANYTHING ELSE WE VIEW WOULD MAKE COMMUNICATION MORE EFFICIENT AND USEFUL FOR ALL.
